The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Mokelumne Hill had a population of 691. The population density was {{convert|224.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Mokelumne Hill was 583 (84.4%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 11 (1.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 4 (0.6%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 3 (0.4%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 12 (1.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 78 (11.3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 85 persons (12.3%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Mokelumne Hill CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0648480 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 326 households, out of which 54 (16.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 142 (43.6%) were married-couple households, 24 (7.4%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 71 (21.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 89 (27.3%) had a male householder with no partner present. 121 households (37.1%) were one person, and 73 (22.4%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.12.<ref name=DP1/> There were 180 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (55.2% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Mokelumne Hill CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0648480 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 122 people (17.7%) under the age of 18, 39 people (5.6%) aged 18 to 24, 139 people (20.1%) aged 25 to 44, 165 people (23.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 226 people (32.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 53.3{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 113.3 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 368 housing units at an average density of {{convert|119.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 326 (88.6%) were occupied. Of these, 223 (68.4%) were owner-occupied, and 103 (31.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

